AGI -&nbsp;&nbsp; To recognise women's work in the rail sector, the European Commission's Women in Transport Platform, the European Railway Partnership (EU-Rail); The European Railway Agency (ERA), the European Railway Community (CER) and the European Railway Trade Union Federation (UNIFE), launch the second edition of the "Women in Rail Award 2024". This award was first launched in 2022, during the European Year of Railways. Since then, other partners have joined the event, making this year's edition even more important.
&nbsp;
The aim of this award is to promote fairness, diversity and equality, as well as &nbsp;celebrate exceptional and stimulating women and their successes in the rail sector. These awards will be awarded in three categories, recognizing the work of women at different levels: 1) The Research and Innovation Award rewards a woman who has done considerable work in the field of research and innovation, thus helping to strengthen the attractiveness and/or competitiveness of the railway sector; 2) the Leadership and Mentoring Award recognizes a woman who has demonstrated exceptional leadership and mentoring through concrete actions, thus helping other women to have a positive impact on the European rail sector; 3) the Women's Empowerment Award rewards European railway companies who have made gender equality an absolute priority. Applicants may apply by 31 May 2024 for any award category. The award ceremony will take place on 25 September 2024 in Berlin, at the European stand in InnoTrans .

